HEADWORD: Tolt
<hw>Tolt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>tolta</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>tollere</ets> to take away.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>A writ by which a cause pending in a court baron was removed into a
country court.</def> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
